Package org.team1540.rooster.motionprofiling

Class ProfileContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.team1540.rooster.motionprofiling.ProfileContainer
  • public class ProfileContainer
extends Object
    Class to preload motion profiles from a specified folder on disk. The preloaded motion profiles are stored in RAM so as to be quickly accessible.

    The folder provided should contain profile CSV files (formatted so as to be read by Pathfinder.readFromCSV(File)) where each profile named name is stored in two files, name_left.csv for the left-side profile and name_right.csv for the right-side profile. An example folder structure would be as follows (where the profiles/ directory is provided to the constructor): 

     profiles/
   foo_left.csv
   foo_right.csv
   bar_left.csv
   bar_right.csv
    This would cause the ProfileContainer to load two profiles named foo and bar.

    This class is immutable after instantiation.
